.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk status" "\*[BKVER]" %E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.\"    =============== Getting BitKeeper status ===============
.SH NAME
bk status \- show repository status
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bk status
.[OPT] \-\-compat
.[ARG] repository
.SH DESCRIPTION
.LP
The
.B bk status
command gives a quick overview of the current (or specified) repository.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP "\-\-compat "
.B \-\-compat
Produce the pre-bk-7.0 format.
.SH OUTPUT
The default output looks something like:
.DS
Repo: hobbes.bitkeeper.com:/home/lm/bk/dev
Nested: 22/22 components present
Push/pull parent: bk://work.bitkeeper.com/dev
	13 csets to be pulled
4 locally modified files
Repo attributes: level=3, GATE, PORTAL
BK version: bk-7.0.1 (repository requires bk-7.0 or later)
.DE
.LP
The compat output looks something like:
.DS
Status for \*(BK repository /u01/package/bk
\*(BK version is bk-beta-14.3 20000302045832 for x86-linux
Built by: lm@work.bitkeeper.com
Built on: Wed Mar  1 21:22:07 PST 2000
Parent repository is bitkeeper.com:/home/bk/one
Pending patches
    61 people have made deltas.
   600 files under revision control.
     3 files not under revision control.
     0 files modified and not checked in.
     0 files with checked in, but not committed, deltas.
.DE
.SH NOTE
The current output format is preliminary and may change in the future.
.SH SEE ALSO
.SA sfiles
.SH CATEGORY
.B Repository
